usage: git prod enter [-r] [--vnext] [-- <module-paths>]
   or: git prod release [-n] [--vlast] [--vtable] [--merge]
       [--(reuse|alpha|beta|rc|rtm)] [-- <module-paths>]

Manage production mode.

commands:
    enter                   checkout actual or next version in specified modules
    release                 release production branches (always recursively)

options:
    -h|--help               display help
    -r|--recursive          visit specified modules recursively
    -n|--dry-run            do not really release
    --vlast                 release last version of submodules (default to next version)
    --merge                 merge released production branch into development branch (default in bundle)
    --vnext                 checkout next version (default to actual version)
    --vtable                force creation of a vtable when startup module is a composite submodule
                            (default is to create a vtable only when the startup module is a bundle
    --reuse                 reuse last version of startup module
    --alpha                 release startup module as alpha version
    --beta                  release startup module as beta version
    --rc                    release startup module as RC version
    --rtm                   release startup module as RTM version (remove pre-release version)
    <module-paths>          specific modules to visit (default to current module)
    
example:
    git prod enter                 # checkout actual version in startup module
    git prod enter --vnext         # checkout next   version in startup module
    git prod enter -r              # checkout actual version in startup module recursively
    git prod enter -- m1 m2        # checkout actual version in child modules 'm1' and 'm2'
    git prod release               # release production branches in current module recursively
    git prod release -- ../m1      # release production branches in sibling module 'm1' recursively
    git prod release --alpha       # release production branches as alpha version
    git prod release --rtm         # release production branches as RTM version
    git prod release --reuse       # release production branches and reuse last version of startup module
    git prod release --vtable      # force creation of a vtable when startup module is composite (even if it's not a bundle)
    git prod release --vlast       # release last version of submodules
